{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"zotero":1,"inscriptions":5},{"title":2,"date":3,"citation":4},"Iscrizioni latine e greche di Catania tardo-imperiale","1958-1959","\u003Cspan>Giacomo Manganaro, «Iscrizioni latine e greche di Catania tardo-imperiale», \u003Ci>Archivio Storico per la Sicilia Orientale\u003C/i> ser.4 vol.11-12 (1959 1958): 5–30\u003C/span>",[6,120,193,245,318,364,408],{"file":7,"uri":7,"title":8,"status":9,"editionAuthor":11,"type":12,"objectType":16,"material":20,"condition":24,"layoutDesc":25,"handNote":32,"date":46,"places":51,"geo":60,"country":64,"region":24,"settlement":65,"repository":66,"idno":70,"textLang":73,"facsimile":77,"provenance":53,"letterHeights":84,"publications":85,"zotero":97,"keywords":109,"html":119},"ISic000083","Funerary inscription for Iulia Florentina",{"_":10},"draft",null,{"_":13,"ana":14,"ref":15},"funerary","#function.funerary","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html",{"_":17,"ana":18,"ref":19},"plaque","#object.plaque","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259",{"_":21,"ana":22,"ref":23},"marble","#material.stone.marble","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html","",{"layout":26},{"p":27,"rs":28,"damage":24},"Thirteen lines of Latin text, filling the available space.",{"_":29,"ana":30,"ref":31},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"lettering":33,"dimensions":34},"Deeply engraved letters, somewhat irregular in height. A is consistently rendered without cross-bar. There is some fluidity between E, L, I and T, either one for the other, or simply rendered by a vertical stroke. Occasional use of ligatures. No interpunctuation.",[35,42],{"type":36,"l":37,"from":38,"to":39,"h":40,"unit":41},"letterHeight","Lines 1-13","line1","line13","15-20","mm",{"type":43,"l":44,"from":38,"to":45,"unit":41},"interlinear","Not measured","line2",{"_":47,"notBefore":48,"notAfter":49,"evidence":50},"First quarter of the 4th century CE (on the basis of the office of 'corrector')",301,329,"office",[52,56],{"_":53,"type":54,"ref":55},"Catina","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462270",{"_":57,"type":58,"ref":59},"Catania","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2525068",[61],[62,63],37.49223,15.07041,"France","Paris",{"_":67,"role":68,"ref":69},"Louvre","museum","https://www.louvre.fr/",{"_":71,"type":72},"MA2994","inventory",{"_":74,"mainLang":75,"languages":76},"Latin","la",[74],{"n":78,"url":79,"height":80,"width":81,"desc":82,"surfaceType":83},"screen","ISic000083_tiled.tif","1500px","1463px","Image reproduced from the Louvre website according to terms and conditions (© 2007 Musée du Louvre, Dist. GrandPalaisRmn / Daniel Lebée/CarineDeambrosis)","front",[],[86,87,87,88,89,90,91,92,93,94,95,96],"Mommsen, 1883, CIL","L'année épigraphique: revue des publications épigraphiques relatives a l'antiquité romaine., 1888-","Agnello, 1953, Silloge di iscrizioni paleocristiane della Sicilia","Manganaro, 1958-1959, Iscrizioni latine e greche di Catania tardo-imperiale","Ducroux, 1975, Catalogue analytique des inscriptions latines sur pierre conservées au Musée du Louvre.","Bonacasa Carra, 1982-1983, Architettura religiosa cristiana nella Sicila del IV secolo-aspetti e problemi","Bitto, 1989, Alcune osservazioni sulla iscrizione di Iulia Florentina (CIL X 7112)","Wilson, 1990, Sicily under the Roman Empire: the archaeology of a Roman province, 36 B.C. - A.D. 535","Manganaro, 1993, Greco nei pagi e latino nelle città della Sicilia romana tra I e VI sec. d.C.","Bitto, 1996, Catania paleocristiana: l'epitaffio di Theodule","Soraci, 2017, Zoilo, Costantino e le fores martyrum catanesi. Ancora sullʼepigrafe di Iulia Florentina",[98,99,99,100,101,102,103,104,105,106,107,108],"GQN8UZSI","R46KDTZX","D9BZFDDR","BVD8KVF7","B9GH52N2","3JCUD6S7","BXBUXASZ","VF9MMBI9","JBI7CI5R","DMBTEE76","UNVPVXUJ",[110,111,112,13,17,21,113,114,115,116,117,118,75],"isic000083","funerary inscription for iulia florentina",{"_":10},"catina","catania","france","paris","louvre","latin","Text encoding: Jonathan Prag, edition source:",{"file":121,"uri":121,"title":122,"status":123,"editionAuthor":11,"type":125,"objectType":129,"material":130,"condition":24,"layoutDesc":132,"handNote":136,"date":152,"places":157,"geo":160,"country":162,"region":163,"settlement":57,"repository":164,"idno":167,"textLang":169,"facsimile":171,"provenance":53,"letterHeights":176,"publications":177,"zotero":181,"keywords":185,"html":192},"ISic000298","Dedication to the Genius of the city of Catania",{"_":124},"edited",{"_":126,"ana":127,"ref":128},"dedication","#function.dedication","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/88.html",{"_":17,"ana":18,"ref":19},{"_":131,"ana":22,"ref":23},"marble (white)",{"layout":133},{"p":134,"rs":135,"damage":24},"The text is preserved intact, over seven lines, although the edge\n                                        of the surviving stone clips the tops of the letters of the first line. The\n                                        letters diminish in size over the first four lines, with a vacat in the second\n                                        half of line four; the final three lines are larger again. The left margin of\n                                        the text is maintained regularly, the right margin varies from line to line.",{"_":29,"ana":30,"ref":31},{"lettering":137,"dimensions":138},"The letters are deeply but somewhat irregularly cut, with some\n                                    internal variation (e.g. A appears with both broken and straight bar; E appears both\n                                    as a tall narrow standard E and as a vertical stroke with a single horizontal bar\n                                    across the middle; V appears both as V and as Y). Interpuncts are mostly absent,\n                                    except after VC and CONS in the final two lines.",[139,142,146,151],{"type":36,"l":140,"from":38,"to":38,"h":141,"unit":41},"Line 1","60-80",{"type":36,"l":143,"from":45,"to":144,"h":145,"unit":41},"Line 2-4","line4","40-60",{"type":36,"l":147,"from":148,"to":149,"h":150,"unit":41},"Line 5-7","line5","line7","50-70",{"type":43,"from":38,"to":45,"unit":41},{"_":153,"notBefore":154,"notAfter":155,"precision":156},"Munatidius is not otherwise known; the mention of three Domini\n                                    requires one of the periods 337—340, 367—378, 379—383, 388—395, 402—408, and 421. A\n                                    precise choice is not possible, but the consensus amongst scholars is for a date in\n                                    the 4th century rather than later.",337,421,"low",[158,159],{"_":53,"type":54,"ref":55},{"_":57,"type":58,"ref":59},[161],[62,63],"Italy","Sicily",{"_":165,"role":68,"ref":166},"Museo Civico di Catania","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/018",{"_":168,"type":72},"2",{"_":74,"mainLang":75,"languages":170},[74],{"n":78,"url":172,"height":173,"width":174,"desc":175,"surfaceType":83},"ISic000298_tiled.tif","4192px","3680px","Photograph of front face by J. Prag",[],[86,87,178,179,180,89,93,94],"Korhonen, 2004, IMusCatania","ILS, 1892-1916","Holm, 1925, Catania antica",[98,99,182,183,184,101,105,106],"2EUC82DH","XHMS9K6S","7VWTI6D2",[186,187,188,126,17,131,113,114,189,190,114,191,118,75],"isic000298","dedication to the genius of the city of catania",{"_":124},"italy","sicily","museo civico di catania","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Vernantibus \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>saeculis d(ominorum) n(ostrorum) \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>Genio splendidae ur-\u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>bis Catinae \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Facundus Porfyrius \n                    Mynatidius\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Facundus\">Facundus\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Porfyrius\">Porfyrius\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Mynatidius\">Mynatidius\u003C/span>\u003C/span> v(ir) c(larissimus) · \u003Cbr id=\"al7-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">7\u003C/span>cons(ularis) · eiusdem \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"file":194,"uri":194,"title":195,"status":196,"editionAuthor":11,"type":197,"objectType":201,"material":202,"condition":24,"layoutDesc":206,"handNote":209,"date":215,"places":219,"geo":222,"country":162,"region":163,"settlement":57,"repository":224,"idno":225,"textLang":227,"facsimile":229,"provenance":53,"letterHeights":233,"publications":234,"zotero":238,"keywords":241,"html":119},"ISic000301","Inscription recording restoration of a nymphaeum",{"_":10},{"_":198,"ana":199,"ref":200},"building","#function.building","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/86.html",{"_":17,"ana":18,"ref":19},{"_":203,"ana":204,"ref":205},"limestone","#material.stone.limestone","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html",{"layout":207},{"rs":208,"damage":24},{"_":29,"ana":30,"ref":31},{"lettering":210,"dimensions":211},"The form of the letter P is distinctive (found also in the letter of\n                                    Iulius Paternus, ISic000308) with a horizontal stroke at the base.",[212,213],{"type":36,"l":140,"from":38,"to":38,"unit":41},{"type":43,"l":214,"from":38,"to":45,"unit":41},"Interlineation line 1 to 2",{"_":216,"notBefore":217,"notAfter":218,"precision":156},"Perhaps middle/later 4th century CE",351,400,[220,221],{"_":